name: lib/interfaces/ipsp.js
IPSP
description: Interface that peer-sampling protocol must implement for this module to work.

name: send
description: Send a message to a peer.

params.name: peerId
params.description: The identifier of the peer to send the message to.

params.name: message
params.description: The message to send.

params.name: retry
params.description:
Retry to send the message once per second
during retry milliseconds

Resolved if the message has been sent, rejected

name: lib/interfaces/iunicast.js
IUnicast
description:
An interface providing easy-to-use event-like functions on top of a
peer-sampling protocol. As soon as protocols register, they get an
interface. They can send messages using unicast.emit('eventName', neighborId,
args) and the neighbor can catch them using unicast.on('eventName', args).

params.name: protocolId
params.description:
The identifier of the protocol that request
the interface.

params.name: parent
params.description: The instanciator.

name: emit
description: Send a message using the emit function.

unknown.tagValue:
{Promise} Resolved if the message seems to have been sent,
rejected otherwise (e.g. timeout, unkown peers).

params.name: event
params.description: The event name.

params.name: peerId
params.description:
The identifier of the peer to send the event
to.

params.name: args
params.description: The arguments of the event.

return.description:
Resolved if the message seems to have been sent,
rejected otherwise (e.g. timeout, unkown peers).

params.name: message
params.description: The message received.

params.name: unicastId
params.description: The identifier of the unicast protocol.

params.name: protocolId

The identifier of the protocol that sent the
message and that will receive the message.

params.name: eventName
params.description: The name of the event to trigger.

params.name: args
params.description: The arguments of the event.

name: lib/unicast.js
Unicast
description:
Unicast component that simply chooses a random peer from a peer-sampling
protocol and send a message.

params.name: psp
params.description: The peer-sampling protocol.

name: register
description: Registers the protocol that wishes to use this module.

unknown.tagValue:
{IUnicast} An interface providing easy-to-use event-like
functions to send and receive messages.

params.name: protocolId
params.description: The identifier of the protocol that registers.

return.description:
An interface providing easy-to-use event-like
functions to send and receive messages.

params.name: protocolId
params.description:
The identifier of the protocol that
unregisters.
